@startuml sequence-read-inbox
!theme plain

title Sequence Diagram: Baca Inbox (Read Folder)

actor "User" as U
participant "Client" as C
participant "AppWrite" as AW
participant "MailController" as MC
participant "MailService" as MS
participant "HrServiceClient" as HR
participant "UserTaskRepository" as UTR
participant "MailRepository" as MR
participant "Cache\n(Caffeine)" as Cache
participant "HR REST API" as HRAPI

U -> C : Open Inbox
C -> MC : GET /api/v1/mails/folders/1/mails\n?page=0&size=20&sort=createdDate,desc\n{Authorization: Bearer JWT}

MC -> MC : Validate JWT via AppWrite
MC -> MS : getMailsByFolder(userId, folderId=INBOX, pageable)

MS -> UTR : findByUserIdAndFolderId(userId, INBOX)
note right
  SELECT m.*, mc.mcat_code, mc.mcat_name,
         ut.read_status, mt.mail_type
  FROM sys_user_task ut
  JOIN mail m ON m.m_id = ut.tm_id
  LEFT JOIN mail_category mc ON mc.mcat_id = m.m_category
  LEFT JOIN mail_type mt ON mt.mail_type_id = m.m_type
  WHERE ut.user_id = :userId
  AND ut.folder_id = :folderId
end note

UTR --> MS : Page<Mail> (20 records)

' No need to call HR API for list view
' because names are denormalized in mail table
note over MS
  **Key Design Decision:**
  m_created_by_name, m_to_str are
  denormalized → No HR API call needed
  for list view. Only call HR API when
  user needs live data (e.g., current position).
end note

MS --> MC : Page<MailSummaryResponse>
MC --> C : 200 OK\n{content: [...], totalElements, totalPages}
C --> U : Render inbox list

@enduml
